FBIS4-43638 "drweu119aa_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-119 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Chernomyrdin on Russia's Participation in G-7 Chernomyrdin on Russia's Participation in G-7 LD2006131494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1242 GMT 20 Jun 94 LD2006131494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] "We are sure that the G-7 will soon become the G-8. This will be an important step on the way to full Russian participation in the world economy," the Russian prime minister said at the opening ceremony of the 19th world congress on gas, currently being held in Milan. Russia expects from the next Naples G-7 summit "concrete proposals to make investments easier," Chernomyrdin said. The Russian prime minister later went to Arcore to meet with Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi.
